verses.text: Adam , Sheth , Enosh ,
Kenan , Mahalaleel , Jered ,
Henoch , Methuselah , Lamech ,
Noah , Shem , Ham , and Japheth. \p
¶ The sons of Japheth ; Gomer , and Magog , and Madai , and Javan , and Tubal , and Meshech , and Tiras.
And the sons of Gomer ; Ashchenaz , and Riphath , and Togarmah.\f + \fr 1.6 \ft Riphath: or, Diphath as it is in some copies\f*
And the sons of Javan ; Elishah , and Tarshish , Kittim , and Dodanim.\f + \fr 1.7 \ft Dodanim: or, Rodanim, according to some copies\f* \p
¶ The sons of Ham ; Cush , and Mizraim , Put , and Canaan.
And the sons of Cush ; Seba , and Havilah , and Sabta , and Raamah , and Sabtecha. And the sons of Raamah ; Sheba , and Dedan.
And Cush begat Nimrod : he began to be mighty upon the earth.
And Mizraim begat Ludim , and Anamim , and Lehabim , and Naphtuhim ,
And Pathrusim , and Casluhim , (of whom came the Philistines ,) and Caphthorim.
And Canaan begat Zidon his firstborn , and Heth ,
The Jebusite also, and the Amorite , and the Girgashite ,
And the Hivite , and the Arkite , and the Sinite ,
And the Arvadite , and the Zemarite , and the Hamathite. \p
¶ The sons of Shem ; Elam , and Asshur , and Arphaxad , and Lud , and Aram , and Uz , and Hul , and Gether , and Meshech.\f + \fr 1.17 \ft Meshech: or, Mash\f*
And Arphaxad begat Shelah , and Shelah begat Eber.

And unto Eber were born two sons : the name of the one \add was\add* Peleg ; because in his days the earth was divided : and his brother’s name \add was\add* Joktan.\f + \fr 1.19 \ft Peleg: that is, division\f*
And Joktan begat Almodad , and Sheleph , and Hazarmaveth , and Jerah ,
Hadoram also, and Uzal , and Diklah ,
And Ebal , and Abimael , and Sheba ,
And Ophir , and Havilah , and Jobab. All these \add were\add* the sons of Joktan. \p
¶ Shem , Arphaxad , Shelah ,
Eber , Peleg , Reu ,
Serug , Nahor , Terah ,
Abram ; the same \add is\add* Abraham. \p
The sons of Abraham ; Isaac , and Ishmael. \p
¶ These \add are\add* their generations : The firstborn of Ishmael , Nebaioth ; then Kedar , and Adbeel , and Mibsam ,
Mishma , and Dumah , Massa , Hadad , and Tema ,\f + \fr 1.30 \ft Hadad: also called, Hadar\f*
Jetur , Naphish , and Kedemah. These are the sons of Ishmael. \p
¶ Now the sons of Keturah , Abraham’s concubine : she bare Zimran , and Jokshan , and Medan , and Midian , and Ishbak , and Shuah. And the sons of Jokshan ; Sheba , and Dedan.
And the sons of Midian ; Ephah , and Epher , and Henoch , and Abida , and Eldaah. All these \add are\add* the sons of Keturah.
And Abraham begat Isaac. The sons of Isaac ; Esau and Israel. \p
¶ The sons of Esau ; Eliphaz , Reuel , and Jeush , and Jaalam , and Korah.
The sons of Eliphaz ; Teman , and Omar , Zephi , and Gatam , Kenaz , and Timna , and Amalek.\f + \fr 1.36 \ft Zephi: or, Zepho\f*
The sons of Reuel ; Nahath , Zerah , Shammah , and Mizzah.
And the sons of Seir ; Lotan , and Shobal , and Zibeon , and Anah , and Dishon , and Ezer , and Dishan.
And the sons of Lotan ; Hori , and Homam : and Timna \add was\add* Lotan’s sister.\f + \fr 1.39 \ft Homam: or, Hemam\f*

The sons of Shobal ; Alian , and Manahath , and Ebal , Shephi , and Onam. And the sons of Zibeon ; Aiah , and Anah.\f + \fr 1.40 \ft Alian: also called, Alvan\f*\f + \fr 1.40 \ft Shephi: also called, Shepho\f*
The sons of Anah ; Dishon. And the sons of Dishon ; Amram , and Eshban , and Ithran , and Cheran.\f + \fr 1.41 \ft Amram: or, Hemdan\f*
The sons of Ezer ; Bilhan , and Zavan , \add and\add* Jakan. The sons of Dishan ; Uz , and Aran.\f + \fr 1.42 \ft Jakan: or, Akan\f* \p

¶ Now these \add are\add* the kings that reigned in the land of Edom before \add any\add* king reigned over the children of Israel ; Bela the son of Beor : and the name of his city \add was\add* Dinhabah.
And when Bela was dead , Jobab the son of Zerah of Bozrah reigned in his stead.
And when Jobab was dead , Husham of the land of the Temanites reigned in his stead.
And when Husham was dead , Hadad the son of Bedad , which smote Midian in the field of Moab , reigned in his stead: and the name of his city \add was\add* Avith.
And when Hadad was dead , Samlah of Masrekah reigned in his stead.
And when Samlah was dead , Shaul of Rehoboth by the river reigned in his stead.
And when Shaul was dead , Baal-hanan the son of Achbor reigned in his stead.

And when Baal-hanan was dead , Hadad reigned in his stead: and the name of his city \add was\add* Pai ; and his wife’s name \add was\add* Mehetabel , the daughter of Matred , the daughter of Mezahab.\f + \fr 1.50 \ft Hadad: or, Hadar\f*\f + \fr 1.50 \ft Pai: or, Pau\f* \p
¶ Hadad died also. And the dukes of Edom were; duke Timnah , duke Aliah , duke Jetheth ,
Duke Aholibamah , duke Elah , duke Pinon ,
Duke Kenaz , duke Teman , duke Mibzar ,
Duke Magdiel , duke Iram. These \add are\add* the dukes of Edom.
